# What is Microting eForm



![](.gitbook/assets/image.png)

XML / JSON is sent from "Your system" to dedicated server at Microting, after which data is prepared for synchronisation on Your system Android/iOS tablets / smartphones.

Your systems employees synchronise their tablet / smartphone via 3G / 4G or Wi-Fi. Data collection takes place offline and is therefore completely independent of functioning Internet connection.

When data is collected, Your systems employee synchronises their tablet / smartphone via 3G / 4G or Wi-Fi, after which collected data is sent to Microting. XML / JSON is prepared as Your system then extracts, extracts and stores.

## **How is the system build up?**



![](.gitbook/assets/image%20%281%29.png)

Android Phone / Phablet / Tablet

Microting InSpection can be run on all Android 8.x / iOS 9.+.

**Synchronization**

On the synchronization screen, the checklists are sent and retrieved via 3G / 4G and / or Wi-Fi. When the checklists are synchronized, all data is collected offline.

**Employees**

If several employees share the same device, employee login screen is displayed. Employee name is chosen, after which documentation can be started.

If there is only one employee attached to the device, the employee login screen will not be displayed.

**Checklist** **Groups**

A checklist group can contain one or more underlying checklist groups. A checklist group contains on the lower level one or more checklists. When all checklist group underlying checklists are completed, the color of the checklist group changes from red to green.

**eForms**

The eForm contain one or more data fields in which the documentation itself is made. When a eForm is completed, the color of the checklist changes from red to green.
